title: My Best Girl
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2ShHh77

by MurasakibaraAoi

Tony can count with one hand the number of things he has wanted in his life, but has never been able to get.
His father’s love and affection was the first thing.
Then, there was Mary Fitzpatrick.

 

As time went by, Peter looked less like Mary and more like Richard. This is something that anyone who had known the Parkers could confirm.
For all Tony cared, genetics could go suck it.
She could grow to have a Parker’s nose and jawline. Peter could have their ears and their horrible taste in baseball teams, could go change her eyes from Mary’s brown to Richard’s green, and none of that would matter. At the end of the day, she was still Tony’s.

summary: Can you please write a fic where DUM-E gets erased in the snap and how that affects tony? Please please pretty please
question: Can you please write a fic where DUM-E gets erased in the snap and how that affects tony? Please please pretty please
answer:
I think this is maybe the cruelest headcanon anyone’s ever dumped on me and I simultaneously want to applaud you and curse you because WHAT THE HELL

In other news:

DUM-E is in Tony’s workshop when it happens.

(Of course he is. He’s been there since Tony’s first gone missing. He was in Tony’s workshop back when Tony first disappeared in Afghanistan too. DUM-E makes a new smoothie every day, because Tony would come back soon, Tony always comes back, and DUM-E wants a smoothie to be ready and fresh because they make Tony smile and pat DUM-E and that’s really all DUM-E wants. Pepper comes by sometimes and DUM-E likes Pepper, but Pepper isn’t Tony. Tony is DUM-E’s favorite. DUM-E doesn’t offer Pepper a smoothie. He makes another one though because Tony always likes them best fresh.)

Meaning that, when Tony finally makes it back from losing the one fight that really matters and he can’t find DUM-E, only a lot of full glasses that are about a month old, and FRIDAY says ‘Boss’ like she’s got more bad news to share – Tony sees it on video.

DUM-E disintegrating. DUM-E struggling to place the smoothie glass on the table so it won’t drop whilst disintegrating into nothingness.

“Tony?” Pepper whispers, warm and worried and teary-eyed.

And Tony thinks of Peter and the desperate fear on his face, the useless pleas, and he thinks of DUM-E pushing that stupid glass on the counter and the beep that isn’t supposed to sound distressed that he can’t unhear and the rest of that team that wasn’t turning to dust, halfway across the universe.

DUM-E isn’t– he wasn’t– he wasn’t meant to– He’d been built to–

*

(Tony is thirteen when he buries Einstein, his cat and closest confidant, the only pet he could convince his mother to allow him. He is thirteen and he doesn’t cry, knows better than to, and so instead he blinks and blinks and blinks until the burning feeling is gone. He’s not gonna do this again, he decides then. He can’t. He won’t.

The next friend he’s going to make himself. The next friend he makes, he’s going to build to last.)

*

[Somewhere, somewhen, someone will remember that a soul cannot be created out of metal and other earthly materials. Somewhere, somewhen, someone will recall that a soul can be shared.

And so in a universe where there is no such thing as soulmates, Tony Stark builds himself one anyways.]

You’re welcome

title: Cuddles
body:
“Do you want anything else?” Tony asked, laying down behind you on the couch. You shook your head as he wrapped an arm around you, pulling you against him. You snuggled up to the blanket watching Supernatural reruns on the television.

It had been a pretty awful day. First, Karen -the newest employee- spilled her burning coffee all over your shirt, causing you bright red bra to stand out. You had rushed to grab your other shirt and change, not realizing that you had knocked your tea all over your paperwork until you came back.

Your boss had then proceeded to demand you turn in all of your paperwork by the end of the day or she would fire you. You ended up skipping lunch to finish all that you had left. When you finally left, you accidentally dropped your phone on the steps leading down to the subway.

In all, your day was horrendous.

It certainly got better however when Tony walked into your shared living room carrying burritos from your favorite Mexican restaurant (you were friends with the chef) and your favorite movies including The Hobbit saga and Star Wars.

You had gotten through all the movies and decided to watch Supernatural until one of you fell asleep. You watched as Dean loaded the shotgun with more salt. You felt Tony’s hand creep up to your hair and began to run his fingers. You relaxed more into his chest, feeling his heartbeat slowly pound and felt his chest move every time he took a breath.

Tony’s other hand slid onto your stomach, permanently resting there. He pulled you head forward slightly, lightly kissing your head a couple times as you focused on the screen.

You felt your heart swell knowing that Tony would always be there, no matter what. That made you happy. Knowing that you could take on the world with your lover right beside you.
